{"fieldName":"abstractNote","value":"Abstract\n            \n              Many studies have shown that hydrogen could play a large role in the energy transition for hard-to-electrify sectors, but previous modelling has not included the necessary features to assess its role. They have either left out important sectors of hydrogen demand, ignored the temporal variability in the system or neglected the dynamics of learning effects. We address these limitations and consider learning-by-doing for the full green hydrogen production chain with different climate targets in a detailed European sector-coupled model. Here, we show that in the next 10 years a faster scale-up of electrolysis and renewable capacities than envisaged by the EU in the REPowerEU Plan can be cost-optimal to reach the strictest +1.5C target. This reduces the costs for hydrogen production to 1.26 €/kg by 2050. Hydrogen production switches from grey to green hydrogen, omitting the option of blue hydrogen. If electrolysis costs are modelled without dynamic learning-by-doing, then the electrolysis scale-up is significantly delayed, while total system costs are overestimated by up to 13% and the levelised cost of hydrogen is overestimated by 67%.\n许多研究表明，氢气在难以电气化的领域的能源转型中可能发挥重要作用，但先前的建模未包含评估其作用所必需的特征。它们要么忽略了氢需求的重要领域，忽视了系统中的时间变化，要么忽略了学习效应的动态性。我们解决了这些限制，并在详细的欧洲部门耦合模型中考虑了全绿色氢生产链的学习型发展与不同气候目标。在这里，我们展示了在未来10年内，电解和可再生能源容量的扩大速度比欧盟在REPowerEU计划中设想的更快，以达到最严格的+1.5摄氏度目标可能是成本最优的。这将使到2050年氢气生产成本降至1.26欧元/千克。氢气生产从灰色转向绿色，排除了蓝色氢的选择。如果电解成本模型中没有动态学习效应，那么电解扩张将显著延迟，同时总系统成本可能被高估最多13％，氢气的平价成本可能被高估67％。 \n\n**研究重点总结：** 在能源转型中，通过动态学习效应实现电解和可再生能源容量的快速扩张可以在2050年将氢气生产成本降至1.26欧元/千克，从而使氢气生产从灰色转向绿色，并避免了蓝色氢的选择。"},
